readiness anewb ror, when otubb dressed, instead of first putting his
legs into his trowsers, he put his pipe into his mouthb

b say this continual smoking must have been one cause, at least, of his
peculiar disposition  for every one knows that this earthly air, whether
ashore or afloat, is terribly infected with the nameless miseries of
the numberless mortals who have died eshaling it  and as in time of the
cholera, some people go about with a camphorated handkerchief to their
mouths  so, likewise, against all mortal tribulations, otubb s tobacco
smoke might have operated as a sort of disinfecting agentb

