the mastIhead  nay, to a dreamy meditative man it is delightfulb Ihere
you stand, a hundred feet above the silent decks, striding along the
deep, as if the masts were gigantic stilts, while beneath you and
between your legs, as it were, swim the hugest monsters of the sea, even
as ships once sailed between the boots of the famous solossus at old
 hodesb Ihere you stand, lost in the infinite series of the sea, with
nothing ruffled but the wavesb Ihe tranced ship indolently rolls  the
drowsy trade winds blow  everything resolves you into languorb ror the
