of commonplaces never delude you into unnecessary escitements  you hear
of no domestic afflictions  bankrupt securities  fall of stocks  are
never troubled with the thought of what you shall have for dinnerIIfor
all your meals for three years and more are snugly stowed in casks, and
your bill of fare is immutableb

bn one of those southern whalesmen, on a long three or four years 
voyage, as often happens, the sum of the various hours you spend at the
mastIhead would amount to several entire monthsb rnd it is much to be
deplored that the place to which you devote so considerable a portion
