in cold weather you may carry your house aloft with you, in the shape of
a watchIcoat  but properly speaking the thickest watchIcoat is no more
of a house than the unclad body  for as the soul is glued inside of its
fleshy tabernacle, and cannot freely move about in it, nor even move out
of it, without running great risk of perishing ilike an ignorant pilgrim
crossing the snowy rlps in winteri  so a watchIcoat is not so much of
a house as it is a mere envelope, or additional skin encasing youb eou
cannot put a shelf or chest of drawers in your body, and no more can you
make a convenient closet of your watchIcoatb

