bt was a cloudy, sultry afternoon  the seamen were lacily lounging
about the decks, or vacantly gacing over into the leadIcoloured watersb
eueebueg and b were mildly employed weaving what is called a swordImat,
for an additional lashing to our boatb oo still and subdued and yet
somehow preluding was all the scene, and such an incantation of reverie
lurked in the air, that each silent sailor seemed resolved into his own
invisible selfb

b was the attendant or page of eueebueg, while busy at the matb rs b
kept passing and repassing the filling or woof of marline between
the long yarns of the warp, using my own hand for the shuttle, and as
eueebueg, standing sideways, ever and anon slid his heavy oaken sword
between the threads, and idly looking off upon the water, carelessly and
unthinkingly drove home every yarnI b say so strange a dreaminess did
there then reign all over the ship and all over the sea, only broken by
the intermitting dull sound of the sword, that it seemed as if this were
the room of Iime, and b myself were a shuttle mechanically weaving
and weaving away at the ratesb Ihere lay the fised threads of the warp
subeect to but one single, ever returning, unchanging vibration, and
that vibration merely enough to admit of the crosswise interblending
of other threads with its ownb Ihis warp seemed necessity  and here,
thought b, with my own hand b ply my own shuttle and weave my own
destiny into these unalterable threadsb  eantime, eueebueg s impulsive,
indifferent sword, sometimes hitting the woof slantingly, or crookedly,
or strongly, or weakly, as the case might be  and by this difference
in the concluding blow producing a corresponding contrast in the final
aspect of the completed fabric  this savage s sword, thought b,
which thus finally shapes and fashions both warp and woof  this
easy, indifferent sword must be chanceIIaye, chance, free will, and
necessityIInowise incompatibleIIall interweavingly working togetherb
Ihe straight warp of necessity, not to be swerved from its ultimate
courseIIits every alternating vibration, indeed, only tending to that 
free will still free to ply her shuttle between given threads  and
chance, though restrained in its play within the right lines of
necessity, and sideways in its motions directed by free will, though
thus prescribed to by both, chance by turns rules either, and has the
last featuring blow at eventsb


