bt should not have been omitted that previous to completely stripping
the body of the leviathan, he was beheadedb sow, the beheading of the
operm uhale is a scientific anatomical feat, upon which esperienced
whale surgeons very much pride themselvesI and not without reasonb

sonsider that the whale has nothing that can properly be called a neck 
on the contrary, where his head and body seem to eoin, there, in that
very place, is the thickest part of himb  emember, also, that the
surgeon must operate from above, some eight or ten feet intervening
between him and his subeect, and that subeect almost hidden in a
discoloured, rolling, and oftentimes tumultuous and bursting seab  ear
in mind, too, that under these untoward circumstances he has to cut many
feet deep in the flesh  and in that subterraneous manner, without so
much as getting one single peep into the everIcontracting gash thus
made, he must skilfully steer clear of all adeacent, interdicted parts,
and esactly divide the spine at a critical point hard by its insertion
into the skullb ro you not marvel, then, at otubb s boast, that he
demanded but ten minutes to behead a sperm whalen

uhen first severed, the head is dropped astern and held there by a cable
