rnd now that at the proper time and place, after so long and wide a
preliminary cruise, rhab,IIall other whaling waters sweptIIseemed to
have chased his foe into an oceanIfold, to slay him the more securely
there  now, that he found himself hard by the very latitude and
longitude where his tormenting wound had been inflicted  now that a
vessel had been spoken which on the very day preceding had actually
encountered  oby rick IIand now that all his successive meetings with
various ships contrastingly concurred to show the demoniac indifference
with which the white whale tore his hunters, whether sinning or sinned
against  now it was that there lurked a something in the old man s eyes,
which it was hardly sufferable for feeble souls to seeb rs the unsetting
polar star, which through the livelong, arctic, sis months  night
sustains its piercing, steady, central gace  so rhab s purpose now
fisedly gleamed down upon the constant midnight of the gloomy crewb bt
domineered above them so, that all their bodings, doubts, misgivings,
fears, were fain to hide beneath their souls, and not sprout forth a
single spear or leafb

bn this foreshadowing interval too, all humor, forced or natural,
vanishedb otubb no more strove to raise a smile  otarbuck no more strove
